## 1. Purpose

The purpose of this license is to let the public read, evaluate, test, study, and improve the DreamGraph software while protecting the Licensor's ability to commercially license the software for production, enterprise, managed-service, OEM, and competitive uses.

## 2. Definitions

For purposes of this license:

- **"Licensor"** means the copyright owner of the Licensed Work.
- **"Licensed Work"** means the DreamGraph software made available under this license, including its source code, object code, build scripts, configuration templates, documentation, and related materials included in the same repository or distribution, but excluding third-party software that is separately licensed.
- **"You"** or **"Your"** means the individual or legal entity exercising rights under this license.
- **"Non-Commercial Use"** means use that is not primarily intended for or directed toward commercial advantage, monetary compensation, internal business operations, delivery of client services, or support of a revenue-generating activity.
- **"Evaluation Use"** means internal testing, review, proof-of-concept work, security review, compatibility assessment, and similar evaluation activity performed solely to decide whether to obtain a commercial license. Evaluation Use does **not** include production use, use for client work, or use to operate any business workflow.
- **"Production Use"** means any use of the Licensed Work with live, business, customer, operational, or revenue-related data, or in support of internal business operations, customer-facing systems, managed services, consulting services, or any real-world operational workload beyond purely experimental or evaluation activity.
- **"Commercial Use"** means any Production Use, any use for a fee or other consideration, any use by or for a for-profit or government entity other than limited Evaluation Use, any use to support internal business operations, any use in client services, any managed or hosted offering, any OEM or embedded distribution, and any use in or for a Competitive Offering.
- **"Competitive Offering"** means any product, service, library, model, platform, hosted offering, extension, agent, framework, runtime, managed service, developer tool, or commercial feature that substantially competes with, replaces, replicates, or exposes material functionality of the Licensed Work.
- **"Managed Service"** means making the Licensed Work, or material functionality of it, available to third parties as a hosted, cloud, SaaS, API, service bureau, platform, or managed offering.
- **"Derivative Work"** means any modified version of the Licensed Work or any work based on the Licensed Work to the extent protected by applicable copyright law.
- **"Open Source Project"** means a project whose source code is publicly available under an OSI-approved license.

- **"Evaluation Use means ALL of the following:"**
   - limited duration
   - limited users
   - non-production
   - internal testing only
   - no customer-facing workloads
   - no revenue-generating use
   - no operational dependency

