## 13. Termination

This license terminates automatically and immediately if You violate this license.

If the Licensor determines that a violation is curable and provides written notice, the Licensor may, at its sole discretion, allow a cure period of up to fifteen (15) days. No cure period is required for:

- Commercial Use without a commercial license;
- Production Use without a commercial license;
- use in a Managed Service;
- use in a Competitive Offering;
- trademark misuse;
- bad-faith conduct; or
- intentional removal of notices or technical protections.

Upon termination, You must immediately:

1. stop all use of the Licensed Work and any Derivative Works based on it;
2. stop all distribution and access;
3. destroy or permanently delete all copies in Your possession or control, except to the extent retention is required by law; and
4. on request, certify compliance in writing.

Sections 3, 5, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11, 13, 14, 15, 16, and 17 survive termination.

